# Experiment No.6 : 

The aim is to implement a operator concept.

A. Write a Java program to demonstrate the right shift (>>) operator. 
B. Write a Java program to demonstrate the left shift (<<) operator. 
C. Write a Java program to find the remainder when one number is divided by another using the modulus 
operator (%). 
D. Write a Java program to find the greater of two numbers using the ternary operator. 

public class RightShift {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int a = 16; 
        int result = a >> 2; 
        System.out.println("Right Shift Result: " + result);
    }
}
public class LeftShift {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int a = 4; 
        int result = a << 2; 
        System.out.println("Left Shift Result: " + result);
    }
}



import java.util.Scanner;

public class ModulusExample{
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        System.out.print("Enter Two Numbers: ");
        int a = sc.nextInt(), b = sc.nextInt();
        System.out.println("Remainder: " + (a % b));
    }
}


import java.util.Scanner;

public class TernaryGreater {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        System.out.print("Enter Two Numbers: ");
        int a = sc.nextInt(), b = sc.nextInt();
        int max = (a > b) ? a : b;
        System.out.println("Greater Number is: " + max);
    }
}
